Three boda boda passengers died on Thursday morning in a head on collision with a car on Narok-Bomet highway.They died at the scene of the 4am accident next to Nyangores river, a kilometre away from Bomet town, said area OCPD Abel Sande.Sande said the accident occurred as the rider tried to overtake a bus; he ended up hitting the car that was headed in the opposite direction.He said the driver of the Guardian bus recorded a statement with police.The accident comes barely a week after a man died in Kapkwen area, some 3km from Bomet town, when a motorcycle collided with a car.The OCPD urged boda boda operators to be careful while overtaking on the highway, saying most accidents involve them.The bodies were taken to Longisa hospital morgue.